Allscripts, Boston Scientific, Friedman Industries: U.S. Equity Preview

-- B y   N i k o l a j   G a m m e l t o f t
-- 
2011-05-27T21:46:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/allscripts-boston-scientific-friedman-u-s-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in U.S. trading May 31. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Allscripts Healthcare Solutions Inc. (MDRX)  : The
provider of electronic health-care record systems is seeing “a
strong uptick in demand,” Chief Executive Officer Glen Tullman
told CNBC. The U.S. government is subsidizing doctors as they
adopt electronic health-care records.  Boston Scientific Corp. (BSX)  : The second-biggest maker
of heart devices said it is voluntarily recalling all of its
iCross Coronary Imaging Catheters used in intravascular
ultrasound imaging.  Friedman Industries (FRD)  Inc: The steelmaker boosted
its quarterly dividend to 13 cents a share from 11 cents a
share. The Bloomberg forecast was 11 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nikolaj Gammeltoft in New York at 
 ngammeltoft@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at   nbaker7@bloomberg.net . 